@NODE "How to use MIS" "How to use MIS"
@TOC "How does MIS work?"
How to use MIS:
---------------

 First choose a function with the cyclegadget. Then drop the 'dest'
icon on the window and after that the 'source' icon. If you just drop
the 'dest' icon then a default icon will be used, depending of what you
have chosen in the menu @{"Default" LINK "The default menu"}, as a 'source' icon.
 Then press the start button.
 You can also drop more than one icon at the time, if you do, remember
to click on the 'dest' icon before the 'source' icon.
 The Reset button is for resetting the textgadgets.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Functions" "Functions"
@TOC "How does MIS work?"
Functions:
----------

 @{B}Copy icon@{UB} is used for copying an icon.  Note! If you are going
to copy for instance a file-icon to a drawer-icon you should
rather use the function Copy image. Otherwise the WB can
think that the drawer is a file.

 @{B}Copy image@{UB} is used to only copy the icons image. The ToolTypes,
coordinates and other will not be changed.

 @{B}Copy ToolTypes@{UB} is used for copying the ToolTypes only. Note that
the old ToolTypes will be overwritten.

 @{B}Delete icon@{UB} is used for deleting an icon.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Autostart" "Autostart"
@TOC "Settings"
Auto start:
-----------

 The chosen function will start automatically when x number of icons
are dropped on the window. The number of icons can be set with the
menu Autostart. 
 @{B}Note!@{UB} Delete icon always starts after @{B}one@{UB} icon have been 
dropped on the window regardless of the number chosen.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "The default menu" "The default menu"
@TOC "How does MIS work?"
The default menu:
-----------------

 The default menu is for setting which icon should be used when
no 'source' icon has been dropped.

 When @{B}OFF@{UB} is chosen then def_disk is used if the
dest icon is a disk, def_drawer if the dest icon is a drawer...

 If you have chosen @{B}Automatic@{UB} then the program checks
what's after the dot and puts 'def_' before it and look in the
drawer ENV:sys/ for a file with that name. Eg: If the file is
called Pic.iff then the program will look for a file called
def_iff and use that icon as a source icon. If the program
don't find a matching file then it will behave the same way as
if you had chosen OFF.

 The following items is a list of all the files in the drawer 
'ENV:sys/' that starts with 'def_'. The file you choose will be
used as a source icon.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "Settings" "Settings"
@TOC "How does MIS work?"
Settings:
---------


 Name                 Description                     Default
 ----                 -----------                     ------

CX_POPUP=<YES|NO>  If the window should popup or not     YES
CX_POPKEY<STRING>  The Commodities HotKey                ctrl alt i  
CX_TOP=<INT>       The windows Y-coordinate               0
CX_LEFT=<INT>      The windows X-coordinate               0
AUTOSTART=<1|2|OFF>@{"Autostart" LINK "Autostart"} after x icons              OFF
                   has been dropped on the window
                   OFF turns the function off.
DEFICON=<INT>      The number of the item in the menu
                   @{"default" LINK "The default menu"} that
                   will be checked at start-up.
FONT=<STRING>      Name of the font to use.               topaz.font
FONTSIZE=<INT>     Size of the font to use.               8
ZOOMED=<YES|NO>    Define if you want the window
                   zoomed at startup.                     NO
                  
@ENDNODE


